      "content": "doctors and support groups... they've tried everything. they just give me more pills that make me feel like a zombie or tell me to \"manage\" it. but how do you manage something that never stops? it's not even about getting better anymore. it's just wanting the noise to stop. the constant, physical noise of the pain. sometimes i just stare at the ceiling and think about how much easier it would be if i just... wasn't here. if everything just went quiet.",
